description:
100-page special! Three incredible adventures in the Marvel Universe!

The new Ms Marvel is here! Kamala Khan is 16, she's just gotten her powers, and she's facing a rogue group of Inhumans! An amazing new series begins by G Willow Wilson and Takeshi Miyazawa!

Daredevil tackles the sinister Stunt-Master! By Mark Waid and Chris Samnee!

The Agents of SHIELD watch as Skye confronts her insane father, Mr Hyde! By Mark Waid and Greg Smallwood!

Featuring material first printed in Ms Marvel #13-15, Daredevil #12 and SHIELD #7.

One scriptwriter, 6 artists, a great people: the dwarves!

In the old days, united under a King, Dwarves thoroughly dominated the mountains. When the great schism split them into a multitude of fortress-states, they divided knowledge between the four main Orders: the Forge, the Talion, the Temple and

the Shield. Then a fifth one was created which included the outcasts and the underprivileged: the Order of the Wanderers.

A golden cube covered in esoteric writings has been dug out from the bowels of a fortress-state of the South. When the Masters of the Order of the Temple arrive, the evil is already awakening, showing the darkest face of the dwarf people.
name: Aral du Temple

volume.name: Ookii Onnanoko wa Daisuki Desu ka?

description:
Are men condemned to be the Gods’ playthings?

They are two brothers, born into a world in ruins where even the Gods seem to be exhausted and about to fade away. Two brothers who are entirely different: one is strong and stupid and ultimately powerless in front of adversity; the other, on the contrary,

dreams only of forgotten knowledge, of voyages and reconquests. For the good of Men, he will go as far as reneging on an old pact by defying Zeus and his powerful wife, Hera.
name: Le Clairvoyant

description: A full-color Manga For Kids series! Corona and Lan have joined the Space Patrol and are ready to help outer space friends in trouble. In this volume, the girls visit a planet full of seemingly friendly aliens who don't want the girls to leave - ever! Plus Corona helps her partner overcome her social awkwardness by inviting Lan on a girls afternoon out. With equal parts space adventure and school hijinks, Swans in Space has something for everyone.
name: Vol. 2

description: A full-color Manga For Kids series! Corona and Lan have joined the Space Patrol and are ready to help outer space friends in trouble. In this volume, the girls visit a space restaurant full of weird and wacky aliens. Plus, Corona learns of a sinister plot that might put all of planet Earth in danger!
name: Vol. 3

description:
76 pages of claw-popping action!

"Three Months to Live" continues as Wolverine finally meets the being he has known all his life – Death! By Paul Cornell and Kris Anka!

Deadpool, Shiklah and Bob face the might of Modok, AIM and a werewolf – and if they survive that, Dracula is waiting! By Gerry Duggan and Reilly Brown!

Featuring material first printed in Wolverine #9 and Deadpool: Dracula's Gauntlet #4-5.

The four-part Assassination Classroom side story continues! Koro-Sensei continues to annoy his would-be assassins by...partying and being nice! And in My Hero Academia, the U.A. tightens the noose around the villains! Plus, a beach party in Black Clover!
